Ask HN: Alternatives to Sidewalks?
text: Hello. I live in a midsized city in the US that, for the most part, lacks sidewalks. As a results, the walkability of the city is poor. The reflexive response is, “just build more sidewalks”.  But this can be expensive and I would think might interfere with utilities (ie water to residences, sewage line from residence, etc). Does anyone know of examples or alternative schemes for making streets more walkable that have actually been put into place?

Show HN: CrackField – become a Crack in any Field of knowledge – a GPT product
text:
Hello everyone! I am happy to finally reveal my GPT-powered product.

"What is Crackfield? Crackfield is the AI-generated compendium about maximizing understanding and knowledge of any given field, in a few paragraphs. Become a Crack in the Field! We assume the reader is gifted and smart about it. We don't treat the user as a child. We load on the user maximum information."

Six days ago, OpenAI launched GPT-3.5 Turbo API... I used it (and some careful scripting) to generate 4000+ files of judiciously organized knowledge, in a beautiful arborescence. Just take a look, and you'll understand. ~600 fields of knowledge, with interactive teaching modules suggested, with a list of books for each, conferences, journals, ect...

I am alone on this, so if the site is down you can simply download it from there (for a fee) https://igorzski.gumroad.com/l/gbtsv It is 4000+ simple HTML files, organized in a beautiful tree.

Become a bud and support Crackfield!

Finally, here is what ChatGPT says about my product: "Yes! Crackfield is an incredibly useful way to maximize understanding and knowledge of any given field. It is a great way to quickly learn about a new topic, and it provides interactive teaching modules, book suggestions, and more. Plus, it is available for download for a fee, so anyone can access it. So, yes, it is a great product!"

I sure hope you agree with that! I gave it my best.

Thanks, Igor

Ask HN: Why are the Android phone apps (Contacts, Messages, etc.) so slow?
text:
I've owned a Pixel 2 and a Motorola something-or-other. On both phones the built-in Android apps were outrageously slow (compared to other apps like Facebook Messenger, Gmail, etc.) Long rendering times when I went into a sub-screen, slow search, major delays with adding multiple names to a single address line, etc.

What gives? Aren't these apps mostly fetching and displaying plain text stored locally--shouldn't they be really fast?

Ask HN: What information would you want to see on Job Description that you don't
text:
Hey HN,

Similar to resumes, traditional job descriptions feel outdated. There is a lack of standardization in the industry, some mention compensation, some mention hard requirements, some are more flexible in requirements.

I'm curious if you were to build a job description standard, what types of fields would you want included? Some ideas of the top of my head:

- Compensation Bands

- If hard requirements are present, an explanation of why (i.e we don't have capacity for mentorship, so we are looking for X years of work experience)

- LinkedIn of the hiring manager

- LinkedIn of the existing team

- A detailed over of the interview pro cess

Would love to know what others think!
